y\nthe aforementioned bias towards detecting Hot Jupiters around young stars\nbefore the planets' tidal destruction. Conclusions. We do not find evidence in\nthe data for Hot Jupiter hosts preferentially being in phase space\noverdensities compared to other stars of similar kinematics, nor therefore for\ntheir originating in birth environments of high stellar density.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 29 Mar 2021 16:36:19 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 29 Nov 2021 13:57:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-03-14"}
