ments are almost Clifford gates, for they\nnormalize the generalized Pauli group up to an extra factor $\\zeta$, which is\nan appropriate square root of a primitive root of unity.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 30 Mar 2021 05:19:49 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 15 Mar 2023 02:02:58 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-03-16"}
